rComments: Great prof! He pushes / expects you to work hard which pays off in the end. He also gives great advice for students interested in graduate school. While he may mark his small assignments harshly, you can make it up in large essays and the midterm. Very good class for junior historians interested in going to grad school.

Had Max for HIS 2100 did not like it because so much work at the archives. However, had him for HIS 3397 very interesting. I like that he looks at the different schools of thought on a historical event and the debates. Great project of looking at the inaccuracies/accuracies in film really fun. Easy exams if you listen in class. Very helpful prof!

Very engaging professor; discusses the period's many debates. He knows his stuff. Looking at history through film for our presentations was an awesome idea. Very approachable and funny ... sometimes :)

What are you all talking about? This prof was the highlight of my semester. What I thought would be a really boring class ended up being my favorite class. How can you say he doesn't take teaching seriously?! He was always prepared, shared from his own experiences, and was always willing to help. I hope to take another class with him again. Thanks!

A difficult class, but not a boring one. He was teaching us about how to be historians, not the most interesting subject, but he made it so. I didn't find him self-absorbed at all. As a new professor, his experiences as a student are still fresh and i LOVED how he shared them with us. Very organized and was ALWAYS available to answer questions.
He's a new prof so he has really high, unrealistic expectations from his students. A tough grader but comments are extremely helpful. Shares a lot about his grad school experiences

Understanding with late assignments and stuff, but a killer marker. I actually slaved over the essay and still got a poor mark. He's really quite ruthless and expects a lot out of his students, too much really.

Tries to make it interesting. Enthusiastic. Friendly. Very self-centred, though, and talks only about the topics he is interested in (French Rev, Quebec). Refers to Quebec as separate from Canada. WAY too many assignments: six papers of various length. Very boring class; common sense. Useless prof if interested in Euro history (other than France).
